      • env

        public Environment env()
        The env method returns a CORBA Environment object. This allows a user to retrieve any exceptions that were thrown during processing of this request. If the remote process throws a known exception i.e. one that has been provided within the ExceptionList parameter then actual exception may be extracted via this function from the UnknownUserException Any that is passed back. If the remote process throws a CORBA system exception or a Java exception then these will also be stored within this env parameter. If the remote process throws a UserException that has not been defined via the ExceptionList then a CORBA UNKNOWN will be thrown containing the typecode of the unknown exception.
        Specified by:
        env in class Request
        Returns:
        an org.omg.CORBA.Environment value
